{"word":"G3980 - πειθαρχέω - peitharchéō - pi-tharkh-eh'-o - Hearken","slug":"G3980","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">πειθαρχέω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>peitharchéō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>pi-tharkh-eh'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Hearken"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C0;&#x03B5;&#x03B9;&#x03B8;&#x03B1;&#x03C1;&#x03C7;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03C9; - peitharcheo&#x0304;</b> - <i>pi-tharkh-eh'-o</i><p/>From a compound of <a href=\"#/G3982\">G3982</a> and <a href=\"#/G757\">G757</a>; to <i>be persuaded</i> by a <i>ruler</i>, that is, (generally) to <i>submit</i> to authority; by analogy to <i>conform</i> to advice: - hearken, obey (magistrates)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G3981\">G3981</a>, <a href=\"#/G3982\">G3982</a>, <a href=\"#/G3988\">G3988</a>, <a href=\"#/G4006\">G4006</a>, <a href=\"#/G543\">G543</a>, <a href=\"#/G544\">G544</a>, <a href=\"#/G545\">G545</a>"}]}